    "recap_headline": "Miami Ohio University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "DeKALB, Ill. \u2013\nThe RedHawks were swept by Northern Illinois Sunday after losing the final game of their series 6-4.\nMarcus Dierks\nwas the top offensive performer for Miami, coming up with two hits on three at-bats. The RedHawks fall to 14-8 (5-4 MAC) with the loss while NIU moves to 13-7 (6-3 MAC).\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nClayton Burke\nthrew two strikeouts and a groundout to hold the Huskies scoreless in the first. A solo homer in the second gave NIU a 1-0 lead.\nMiami responded with a run of their own in the third as\nMatthew Buffington\nhit a solo home run to right-center to lead off the inning.\nAfter a double by\nHayden Christiansen\n,\nDiego Cruz\nblasted a home run to right field to put Miami up 3-1 in the fourth.\nThe Huskies capitalized on three hits and two errors in the bottom of the fifth to tie the game at three runs apiece. In the sixth, they hit their second home run of the day, a solo shot, to reclaim the lead at 4-3.\nNIU scored an insurance run in both the seventh and eighth innings, taking their largest lead of the game at 6-3.\nA single, walk, and HBP loaded the bases for the RedHawks in the ninth with no outs.\nEvan Appelwick\nhit a sac fly to score one run, but Miami was unable to close the rest of the gap, rounding out the 6-4 loss.\nMIAMI GAME NOTES:\nDierks went 2-for-3 with a walk and a stolen base.\nAppelwick went 1-for-2 with two walks and an RBI.\nCruz had two RBIs.\nUP NEXT:\nMiami will head to Dayton on Tuesday, March 24 to face the Flyers at 3 p.m. They will then travel to Kent State for a three-game series beginning on Friday, March 27.",
    "watch_url": "https://niuhuskies.com/watch/?Live=6432&type=Live"
  },
